Among social media users, those with higher education report greater heavy usage (51 percent) compared to those with secondary education and below (41 percent). Conversely, those with secondary education and below are found to use social media slightly more moderately (2 hours in a day) than those with higher education ($\Delta$ = 7 percent). This demonstrates that education attainment may be associated with the level of social media usage particularly among heavy users.

\medskip

The difference in the duration of social media usage is greater between age groups. Almost six-in-ten (58 percent) of 18 to 30-year-olds report heavy usage of social media, while the same is found among only three-in-ten (32 percent) of those above 30 years old ($\Delta$ = 26 percent). Likewise, moderate usage (2 hours in a day) is more frequent among those above 30 years old than 18 to 30-year-olds ($\Delta$ = 22 percent). 

